      {
        "step_no": 1,
        "text": "Make the tzatziki: combine yogurt, grated cucumber (squeezed dry), minced garlic, chopped dill or parsley, vinegar, half the salt and a pinch of black pepper in a bowl; mix, taste and adjust seasoning. Refrigerate while you prep other components.",
        "time_min": 8
      },
      {
        "step_no": 2,
        "text": "Marinate the halloumi: whisk together olive oil, lemon juice, dried oregano, minced garlic, remaining salt and pepper in a shallow dish; add halloumi slices and turn to coat. Let sit at room temperature briefly while you heat the pan or grill.",
        "time_min": 5
      },
      {
        "step_no": 3,
        "text": "Prepare vegetables and breads: slice tomatoes and red onion, shred lettuce, and warm flatbreads in a dry skillet or oven until pliable. Keep vegetables ready for assembly.",
        "time_min": 5
      },
      {
        "step_no": 4,
        "text": "Cook the halloumi: heat a nonstick or cast-iron skillet over medium-high heat with remaining oil; add halloumi slices in a single layer and sear 2–3 minutes per side until deep golden brown and crisp. Work in batches if needed.",
        "time_min": 6
      },
      {
        "step_no": 5,
        "text": "Assemble wraps: spread tzatziki down the center of each warmed flatbread, layer lettuce, tomato slices, red onion, and 2–3 slices of hot halloumi. Sprinkle with chopped parsley and optional red pepper flakes, then fold or roll to serve with lemon wedges.",
        "time_min": 4
      },
      {
        "step_no": 6,
        "text": "Serve immediately while halloumi is warm, offering extra lemon and tzatziki on the side.",
